## 1. High-Level Architecture

| Layer | Current Implementation | Evidence |
|---|---|---|
| **Frontend Framework** | React 19 + TypeScript (Vite 7) | `package.json` → `"react": "^19.2.0"`, `vite.config.ts` |
| **Backend Framework** | **None** — fully client-side SPA | No server directory, no API routes, no `express`/`fastapi`/etc. |
| **Database** | **None** — all state is in-memory (RAM) | `CacheService` uses `Map<string, CacheEntry>` in `cache.service.ts` |
| **Storage System** | Browser Memory + `Object URL` (blob) | `FileService.createObjectUrl()` in `file.service.ts` |
| **Authentication** | **None** | No auth library, no login route |
| **3D Rendering Engine** | Three.js `^0.159.0` + React Three Fiber `^9.2.3` | `package.json`, `CanvasRoot.tsx` uses `<Canvas>` from `@react-three/fiber` |
| **State Management** | Zustand `^4.5.0` — single global store | `store/configurator.store.ts` — `useConfiguratorStore` |
| **API Architecture** | **None** — no REST, no GraphQL, no WebSocket | Pure in-browser data flow |
| **Styling** | Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui components | `tailwind.config.ts`, `components/ui/` |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a **pure frontend application with zero backend**. Every piece of state lives in a React + Zustand in-memory store. Nothing is persisted beyond the browser session.

