## 4. Domain Model Analysis

### ConfigMesh
- **Purpose:** Represents a single `THREE.Mesh` within the loaded model.
- **File:** `src/types/ConfigMesh.ts`
- **Fields:** `id` (string), `name` (string), `visible` (boolean), `materialId` (string), `ref` (THREE.Mesh)
- **Database Tables:** None (in-memory)
- **Related APIs:** None
- **Related UI Pages:** `MeshPanel.tsx` (list), `VisibilityToggle.tsx` (action)

### ConfigMaterial
- **Purpose:** Represents a material extracted from the model, with color and texture map metadata.
- **File:** `src/types/ConfigMaterial.ts`
- **Fields:** `id`, `name`, `color` (hex string), `ref` (THREE.Material), texture map booleans (5 flags), texture preview data URLs (5 fields)
- **Database Tables:** None
- **Related APIs:** None
- **Related UI Pages:** `MaterialPanel.tsx`, `ColorControl.tsx`, `TextureMapIndicator.tsx`

### ConfigModel
- **Purpose:** Wrapper holding scene metadata and animation clips.
- **File:** `src/types/ConfigModel.ts`
- **Fields:** `id`, `name`, `url`, `scene` (THREE.Group), `meshCount`, `materialCount`, `animations[]`, `hasAnimations`
- **Database Tables:** None
- **Related APIs:** None
- **Related UI Pages:** `TopBar.tsx` (model name display)

### AnimationClip
- **Purpose:** Wraps a `THREE.AnimationClip` with a UI-facing `id` and `name`.
- **File:** `src/types/ConfigModel.ts`
- **Fields:** `id`, `name`, `duration`, `clip` (THREE.AnimationClip)
- **Related UI Pages:** `AnimationPanel.tsx`

### ConfiguratorState (Zustand Store)
- **Purpose:** Global runtime state for the entire application.
- **File:** `src/store/configurator.store.ts`
- **Key Fields:** `modelUrl`, `modelName`, `scene`, `meshes[]`, `materials[]`, `animations[]`, `currentAnimationId`, `animationSpeed`, `animationTime`, `isAnimationPlaying`, `isLoading`, `hdriIntensity`, `fitCameraRequest`
- **Database Tables:** None — all in-memory, reset on page reload.

> [!WARNING]
> There is **no User entity, no Project entity, no Guide entity, no Step entity**. The application has no concept of persistent user work, saved projects, or workflow states.

