## 8. Mesh Selection Assessment

**Verdict: Infrastructure to identify meshes exists. Click-detection (raycasting) does not exist.**

### What Exists

| Capability | Status | Evidence |
|---|---|---|
| Detect clicked meshes | ❌ Not implemented | No `onPointerDown`, no `Raycaster`, no intersection logic anywhere |
| Access mesh names | ✅ Available | `ConfigMesh.name` stored in Zustand; sourced from `node.name` in `ModelParser.ts:88` |
| Access mesh IDs | ✅ Available | `ConfigMesh.id` — unique UUID-like string generated by `ThreeUtils.generateId()` in `ModelParser.ts:87` |
| Store mesh references | ✅ Available | `ConfigMesh.ref` is the live `THREE.Mesh` object, stored in Zustand `store.meshes[]` |

### Exact Files Involved

- **`src/types/ConfigMesh.ts`** — Defines the `ConfigMesh` interface with `id`, `name`, `visible`, `materialId`, `ref`
- **`src/three/ModelParser.ts` (lines 85–95)** — Creates `ConfigMesh` entries during model traversal
- **`src/store/configurator.store.ts` (lines 32, 50–51)** — Stores `meshes: ConfigMesh[]` and exposes `setMeshes()`, `toggleMeshVisibility()`
- **`src/three/CanvasRoot.tsx`** — The `<Canvas>` element where `onPointerDown` must be added for raycasting
- **`src/three/useConfiguratorScene.ts`** — Where raycasting hook should be integrated (has access to `useThree`)

### Implementation Path for Raycasting

The raycasting capability is **1 hook away**. Since all mesh `ref` objects are already stored in Zustand:

```
useThree().raycaster.intersectObjects(store.meshes.map(m => m.ref))
→ intersects[0].object → match back to ConfigMesh by .ref
→ dispatch setSelectedMesh(meshId) to new store slice
```

