## 10. Database Assessment

### Current Schema Summary
**There is no database.** All data is held in JavaScript heap memory via a Zustand store. State resets completely on page refresh. The only "persistence" is the browser's `Object URL` blob (which is also volatile).

### Proposed ShowaTech Database Schema

```sql
-- Models (uploaded CAD files)
CREATE TABLE models (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(255),
  original_filename VARCHAR(255),
  format VARCHAR(10),        -- glb, gltf, fbx, obj
  storage_url TEXT,          -- S3/Azure blob URL
  uploaded_by UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  uploaded_at TIMESTAMP,
  file_size_bytes BIGINT
);

-- Guides (work instruction documents)
CREATE TABLE guides (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  model_id UUID REFERENCES models(id),
  title VARCHAR(255),
  description TEXT,
  aircraft_type VARCHAR(100),
  status VARCHAR(20),        -- draft | under_review | published
  version INTEGER DEFAULT 1,
  created_by UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  created_at TIMESTAMP,
  published_at TIMESTAMP
);

-- Steps (individual instruction steps within a guide)
CREATE TABLE steps (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  guide_id UUID REFERENCES guides(id),
  step_number INTEGER NOT NULL,
  title VARCHAR(255),
  instruction_text TEXT,
  animation_clip_name VARCHAR(255), -- maps to THREE.AnimationClip.name
  camera_position JSONB,     -- {x, y, z}
  camera_target JSONB        -- {x, y, z}
);

-- Step Mesh Targets (which model regions are highlighted per step)
CREATE TABLE step_mesh_targets (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  step_id UUID REFERENCES steps(id),
  mesh_name VARCHAR(255),    -- maps to ConfigMesh.name / THREE.Mesh.name
  highlight_color VARCHAR(7) -- hex color
);

-- Annotations (3D spatial labels within a step)
CREATE TABLE annotations (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  step_id UUID REFERENCES steps(id),
  label TEXT,
  type VARCHAR(20),          -- info | warning | caution | action
  world_x FLOAT, world_y FLOAT, world_z FLOAT,
  normal_x FLOAT, normal_y FLOAT, normal_z FLOAT,
  mesh_name VARCHAR(255)
);

-- Users
CREATE TABLE users (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  email VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE,
  name VARCHAR(255),
  role VARCHAR(20)           -- author | reviewer | viewer | admin
);
```

### What Changes Are Required
- All data currently in Zustand RAM must be persisted to the above tables
- A REST/GraphQL backend must be built to expose CRUD on Guide, Step, Annotation
- Model files must move from blob Object URLs to a cloud storage bucket
- A `GuideStore` and `StepStore` Zustand slice must be added alongside the existing `ConfiguratorState`

