## 14. Recommended Migration Plan

### Phase 0 — Foundation (Week 1–2)

1. **Audit mesh naming conventions** in existing aerospace CAD files — ensure model parts have meaningful names (e.g., `Screw_Panel_A_01` not `Mesh_001`)
2. **Design the HoloLens Runtime JSON schema** — agree on the exact format with the Unity/HoloLens developer team
3. **Select backend stack** — recommend Node.js + PostgreSQL + S3/Azure Blob Storage
4. **Set up project skeleton** — monorepo with `frontend/` (existing Vite app) + `backend/` (new server)

### Phase 1 — Backend Foundation (Week 3–5)

5. **Implement backend database** — deploy PostgreSQL with the schema from Section 10
6. **Implement model upload API** — `POST /api/models`, store to S3, return signed URL
7. **Implement authentication** — JWT-based login, user roles (author/viewer)
8. **Connect `LoaderService`** to load from server URL instead of blob — change `loadGlb(serverUrl)` call path

### Phase 2 — Raycasting + Mesh Selection (Week 5–6)

9. **Add `onPointerDown` to `CanvasRoot.tsx`** — integrate R3F pointer events
10. **Build `useMeshSelection` hook** — raycaster intersects `store.meshes.map(m => m.ref)`, dispatches `selectedMeshId` to new store slice
11. **Add visual highlight** on selected mesh — overlay emissive color using `ConfigMesh.ref.material`
12. **Test with actual aerospace GLB model** — verify mesh names are accessible

### Phase 3 — Guide + Step Authoring (Week 7–10)

13. **Add `GuideSlice` to Zustand** — `currentGuide`, `steps[]`, `currentStepIndex`
14. **Build Step List Panel** — replaces Statistics tab in `Inspector.tsx`, renders ordered step list
15. **Build Step Editor** — text input for instruction, linked mesh highlight, animation clip selector
16. **Build Guide Wizard** — modal to create/name a guide, select model
