## Summary

The codebase provides a **solid 3D viewing and mesh-inspection foundation** built on a production-quality stack (React 19 + Three.js + React Three Fiber + Zustand). The rendering engine, model loading pipeline, mesh extraction, and animation system are all directly reusable.

However, the **entire ShowaTech domain layer is absent**:
- No backend, no database, no authentication
- No raycasting (the single most critical missing piece)
- No annotation system
- No guide/step/workflow concept
- No HoloLens export format

The recommended strategy is to **keep the 3D frontend intact** and build the authoring workflow on top of it, while constructing a full backend from scratch. The migration is achievable in approximately **14–16 weeks** for a POC.
